article.description: Lexi Held hit five of DePaul's season-high 18 3-pointers and the No. 11 Blue Demons rolled to a 92-66 win over Georgetown on Sunday.
article.headline: No. 11 DePaul women hit 18 3s, sinks Georgetown 92-66
article.linkText: No. 11 DePaul women hit 18 3s, sinks Georgetown 92-66
article.story:
CHICAGO --  Lexi Held hit five of DePaul's season-high 18 3-pointers and the No. 11 Blue Demons rolled to a 92-66 win over Georgetown on Sunday.

Kelly Campbell had four 3s and 14 points and reserve Dee Bekelja had three and 13 points for DePaul (19-2, 9-0 Big East Conference), which has won 10 straight. Deja Church added 12 points, Chante Stonewall 11 and Sonya Morris 10.

Stonewall had eight rebounds, Campbell had seven rebounds and eight assists and Church had three steals.

The Blue Demons had six triples in the first quarter and were 12 of 22 overall, racing to a 32-15 lead. The Hoyas shot 30%.

Church had a two layups and a 3-pointer to start a 13-0 run over the middle of the first quarter that pushed the lead to 20-7. Held and Campbell closed it with 3 pointers.

Brianna Jones, Anita Kelava and Taylor Barnes scored 10 points each for the Hoyas (4-16, 1-8).
